Amgen Inc. (AMGN) Position Cut by Mercer Capital Advisers Inc.

					Posted by Brian Himes on Jul 23rd, 2017 // No Comments 



Mercer Capital Advisers Inc. reduced its stake in shares of  Amgen Inc. (NASDAQ:AMGN) by 11.9% during the first quarter, according to its most recent Form 13F filing with the SEC. The fund owned 5,183 shares of the medical research companyâ€™s stock after selling 700 shares during the period. Mercer Capital Advisers Inc.â€™s holdings in Amgen were worth $850,000 at the end of the most recent reporting period. 
Other large investors also recently added to or reduced their stakes in the company. Hall Capital Management Co. Inc. bought a new stake in  Amgen during the fourth quarter valued at $366,000.  Bingham Osborn & Scarborough LLC boosted its position in shares of  Amgen by 3.7% in the fourth quarter. Bingham Osborn & Scarborough LLC now owns 2,494 shares of the medical research companyâ€™s stock worth $365,000 after buying an additional 89 shares in the last quarter.  Quinn Opportunity Partners LLC acquired a new position in shares of  Amgen during the fourth quarter worth approximately $2,720,000.  MUFG Americas Holdings Corp boosted its position in shares of  Amgen by 0.4% in the fourth quarter. MUFG Americas Holdings Corp now owns 84,435 shares of the medical research companyâ€™s stock worth $12,345,000 after buying an additional 298 shares in the last quarter.  Finally, Vontobel Swiss Wealth Advisors AG boosted its position in shares of  Amgen by 439.7% in the fourth quarter. Vontobel Swiss Wealth Advisors AG now owns 11,495 shares of the medical research companyâ€™s stock worth $1,681,000 after buying an additional 9,365 shares in the last quarter. Institutional investors and hedge funds own  78.80% of the companyâ€™s stock. 


 Get Amgen Inc. alerts:



Amgen Inc. (NASDAQ AMGN) traded up 0.50% during midday trading on Friday, reaching $180.21. 2,674,714 shares of the company traded hands. The stock has a market capitalization of $132.53 billion, a P/E ratio of 17.12 and a beta of 1.36. Amgen Inc. has a 12-month low of $133.64 and a 12-month high of $184.21. The company has a 50 day moving average of $169.47 and a 200-day moving average of $165.39. 




Amgen (NASDAQ:AMGN) last posted its quarterly earnings results on Wednesday, April 26th. The medical research company reported $3.15 EPS for the quarter, topping analystsâ€™ consensus estimates of $3.00 by $0.15. The business had revenue of $5.46 billion during the quarter, compared to analystsâ€™ expectations of $5.60 billion. Amgen had a net margin of 34.42% and a return on equity of 29.37%. The businessâ€™s quarterly revenue was down 1.1% on a year-over-year basis. During the same period last year, the company posted $2.90 earnings per share.  Equities analysts anticipate that  Amgen Inc. will post $12.47 EPS for the current fiscal year. 
